T","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French and Channel Islands (Guernsey and Jersey): from the Old French (Norman) personal name <i>Maug(i)er</i>, <i>Malg(i)er</i>, from ancient Germanic <i>Madalgar(i)</i>, <i>Malger</i>, composed of the elements <i>madal</i> ‘council, meeting’ and <i>gar(i)</i> ‘spear’, or from <i>Amalgar(i)</i>, with the first element <i>amal</i> ‘capable, brave, eager’. Compare   Major  ,   Monger  , and   Munger  .","Probably also an altered form of German   Mager  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Maugeri","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Carmine, Ignazio, Salvatore, Angelo, Camillo, Giuseppe, Orazio, Pietro.","Italian (southern):","variant of <b>Malgeri</b>, from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Madalgari</i> or <i>Amalgari</i> (see   Mauger  )."]},{"name":"Major","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the personal name <i>Malg(i)er</i>, <i>Maug(i)er</i>, an Old French form of ancient Germanic <i>Madalgar(i)</i> (see   Mauger  ).","Hungarian: from a shortened form of <i>majorosgazda</i> (see   Majoros  ) or a derivative of German   Meyer  .","Polish, Czech, and Slovak: from the military rank <i>major</i> (derived from Latin <i>maior</i> ‘greater’), a word related to English <i>mayor</i> and the German surname   Meyer  ."]},{"name":"Mangieri","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Gaspar, Mario, Angelo, Arsenio, Mafalda, Orazio, Rocco, Silvio.","Italian: variant of <b>Malgeri</b>, from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Madalgari</i> or <i>Amalgari</i> (see   Mauger  )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Mauger Vavasour was born about 1310, in Denton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of William Le Vavasour and Agnes Grimston. He married Margaret about 1326, in Denton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1310–":"umbes 1310–Surnud","1310–Male":"1310–Surnud","1329–Male":"1329–Surnud","1